    rationale: "Airway risk assessment requires integration of multiple findings. Torus palatinus can obstruct oral airway placement. Tonsillar hypertrophy narrows the oropharyngeal space, reducing the working area for laryngoscopy and potentially worsening the Mallampati view. Mallampati class III already predicts reduced visualization of pharyngeal structures. Together, these findings compound the risk of difficult mask ventilation and difficult laryngoscopy, warranting a more cautious airway plan \u2014 potentially including video laryngoscopy or preparation for awake intubation. No single finding alone mandates awake fiberoptic intubation, but the combination elevates overall risk.",
